2 A curve passes through the point with coordinates \(\left(\frac{1}{2} \pi, 5\right)\) and is such that \(\frac{\mathrm{d} y}{\mathrm{~d} x}=4 \sec ^{2}\left(\frac{1}{2} x\right)\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 115, 361, 134]]<|/det|>
Find the equation of the curve.

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[77, 71, 97, 88]]<|/det|>
3

<|ref|>image<|/ref|><|det|>[[370, 91, 628, 263]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 277, 918, 298]]<|/det|>
The diagram shows the curves \(y=\mathrm{e}^{2 x}\) and \(y=8 \mathrm{e}^{-x}\). The shaded region is bounded by the two curves and the \(y\)-axis.

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 326, 774, 343]]<|/det|>
(a) Show that the \(x\)-coordinate of the point of intersection of the two curves is \(\ln 2\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 572, 430, 589]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[80, 76, 697, 105]]<|/det|>
4 A curve has equation \(y=\frac{4 \sin x}{3+\cos 2 x}\) for values of \(x\) such that \(0 \leqslant x \leqslant 2 \pi\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 119, 231, 151]]<|/det|>
(a) Find \(\frac{\mathrm{d} y}{\mathrm{~d} x}\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 312, 653, 331]]<|/det|>
(b) Hence find the coordinates of the stationary points of the curve.

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[80, 76, 727, 95]]<|/det|>
5 (a) Sketch on the same diagram the graphs of \(y=|2 x-3|\) and \(y=\ln (x+1)\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 324, 863, 341]]<|/det|>
The \(x\)-coordinates of the points where the graphs intersect are denoted by \(\alpha\) and \(\beta\), where \(\alpha<\beta\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 355, 424, 372]]<|/det|>
(b) Show that \(\alpha=1.5-0.5 \ln (\alpha+1)\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 478, 918, 497]]<|/det|>
(c) Use an iterative formula, based on the equation in part (b), to find the value of \(\alpha\) correct to 3 significant figures. Give the result of each iteration to 5 significant figures.

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 708, 515, 729]]<|/det|>
(d) Show by calculation that \(2.055<\beta<2.065\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[80, 76, 793, 97]]<|/det|>
6 (a) Find the quotient and remainder when \(18 x^{3}-6 x^{2}-30 x+4\) is divided by \((3 x-1)\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 283, 918, 321]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[80, 74, 918, 92]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 74, 697, 93]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 445, 620, 464]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>equation<|/ref|><|det|>[[394, 472, 603, 497]]<|/det|>

\]

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[156, 507, 918, 525]]<|/det|>
